name: WARDENCLYFFE TOWER
description:
I'm a big fan of Nikola Tesla. I decided to complete his tower. What if this curious bit of science had been allowed to exist?

Here's more on the tower from the web - 

Wardenclyffe Tower (1901â€“1917) also known as the Tesla Tower, was an early wireless transmission tower designed by Nikola Tesla in Shoreham, New York and intended for commercial trans-Atlantic wireless telephony, broadcasting, and proof-of-concept demonstrations of wireless power transmission. It was never fully operational, and the tower was demolished in 1917.
